Reasoning: The paper deals with the computational complexity of a mathematical measure of resilience in the face of targeted node attacks for arbitrary degree networks. This topic is closely related to graph theory, network analysis, and optimization, which are all covered by the above-listed arXiv CS sub-categories. Specifically, cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) are the most likely categories, as they directly relate to the mathematical and computational aspects of the problem. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) are also relevant, as they deal with the analysis and optimization of complex networks.
